\pard\f0\fs28 Perennial herbs, more or less woody below. Leaves alternate, 2- to 3-pinnatisect, ultimate segments linear to obovate. Inflorescence cymose, bracteate, Sepals and petals 4, or frequently 5 in the central flower. Petals cucullate, yellow, dentate or ciliate or more rarely entire. Stamens twice as many as the petals; filaments glabrous, attenuate. Capsule 4- to 5-lobed, dehiscent. Styles connate.
\par

