\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 4. R. graveolens} L., {\i Sp. Pl.} 383 (1753). Glabrous throughout; stem 14-45 cm. Lower leaves more or less long-petiolate, the uppermost subsessile; ultimate segments 2-9 mm wide, lanceolate to narrowly oblong or obovate. Inflorescence rather lax; pedicels as long as or longer than the capsule; bracts lanceolate, leaf-like. Sepals lanceolate, acute. Petals oblong-ovate, denticulate, undulate. Capsule glabrous; segments somewhat narrowed above to an obtuse apex. {\i Balkan peninsula and Krym; perhaps elsewhere in Mediterranean region; widely naturalized from gardens in S. & S.C. Europe}. Al *Bl Bu Ga *Hs Ju Rs (K) Tu [Au Co Cz Ga Ge Gr He Hu It Rm].
